{{Unreferenced|date=August 2007}}
The '''United Democratic Forces''' (''Forces Démocratiques Unies'') was an alliance of [[political party|political parties]] in the [[Republic of the Congo]], led by [[Denis Sassou-Nguesso]]. Sassou-Nguesso, presidential candidate of both the [[Congolese Labour Party]] and the FDU, won the [[Republic of the Congo presidential election, 2002|presidential election]] of 10 March 2002 with 89.4% of the vote. In the [[Republic of the Congo parliamentary election, 2002|parliamentary election]] held on 26 May and 20 June 2002, the FDU won 30 out of 153 seats.
